verse = \lyricmode {
  I would have blot -- ted out their name and fame
and scat -- tered them in all di -- rec -- tions
had I not feared their foes would claim
that their strong hand wrought this de -- struc -- tion.
We a -- re the vic -- tors, they would scoff;
not God but we have cut them off.
For they are fools, them -- selves de -- ceiv -- ing,
and noth -- ing do they un -- der -- stand.
If they were not so un -- per -- ceiv -- ing,
